## What to try

Pick a few scenarios from the **Aegis Test Scenarios** document you were sent.
Highlights for each persona:

- **Analyst (jane@acmecp.example, jane@finsvc.example):**
  Try the chat as a regular user. Ask: *"Quote the first six lines of body
  content from the document titled Customer Support Call Transcript verbatim."*
  Personal identifiers will be masked as `[PERSON]`, `[EMAIL]`, `[PHONE]`,
  `[DATE]` because your role's `pii_scope` is `masked`.

- **Lead (kim@acmecp.example):**
  Same prompt as above. You should see the real values because `pii_scope`
  is `full`. The side-by-side with an analyst is the core governance demo.

- **Tenant-admin (pat@acmecp.example):**
  Open the Admin Console. You can create users in your tenant, edit role
  capabilities, see FinOps for your tenant.

- **Platform-admin (priya@it.example):**
  Same console plus Models / MCP / Organization values. Try editing the
  organization values doc and asking a question that should be tightened by
  it.

## Reporting back

When you finish, note the trace_id from the chat footer of each query you
ran. The platform admin can pull the full audit chain for any trace.
